        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Count the Crimes to Cut Act of 2021</strong></p> <p>This bill establishes public databases of federal criminal offenses. </p> <p>Specifically, the bill requires the Department of Justice to report on and create a public database of all criminal statutory offenses. Additionally, the bill requires federal agencies to report on and create public databases of criminal regulatory offenses that they enforce.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
